tle> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udigz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Digz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(3/27/02 12:37:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1073.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.cogeco.ca/~digger/cdnflag.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Was AA what you expected?  </span><hr size=1> I can't agree with people that say it takes too long to get AA xp.  What do you want?  Do you want all of the AA abilites right away?  Hell, at least this gives you something to work towards.<br><br>Before AA came out, level 60 players still played, adventured, etc, and got diddly for it other than loot.  Now at least there's a purpose to hunting with those toons.<br><br>Everyone wants level 60, best loots, and all sorts of power.  You gotta work for it, invest the time.  People are PLing to 50 in like a week now, it's sick.  Verant has slowed down the rate at which you can gain something to what I feel is a reasonable amount.<br><br>Would you be happier if aa took half as long and you got all of your abilities in 2-3 months of normal playing?   Hell, at the rate I'm going, it'll take me a few years to get them, and I'm happy about it. <p><b><i><font face="arial" size="4" color="#ffcc00">Digz Graavz</font></i></b><br><img src="http://home.cogeco.ca/~digger/DBN.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F25><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukronx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kronx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(3/27/02 12:49:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1073.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Was AA what you expected?  </span><hr size=1> Well, as I said above, I don't think anyone should ever get ALL of the AA abilities. But I do think they should take less time. That's why I like the branching idea.<br><br>Honestly, I doubt I'll ever even be a baron, as I level incredibly slow, seeing as I spend my time raiding, traveling, and on alts.<br><br>It's a shame that AA points are balanced around PLers and not the majority of folks who play the game. I know it HAS to be this way, but it IS a shame. <p><img border="0" src="http://www.mindspring.com/~smullen/images/sigtmp.jpg" width="250" height="128"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/unosfentaru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nosfentaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Flamer</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(3/27/02 1:58:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1073.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Was AA what you expected?  </span><hr size=1> Digz...you say....<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  I can't agree with people that say it takes too long to get AA xp. What do you want? Do you want all of the AA abilites right away? Hell, at least this gives you something to work towards.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>I'm a Paladin.  As a Paladin I have 320 total AA Points.  <br><br>I gain about 6 AA/month.  That's with a large amount of played time.  <br><br>So it'd take me 50 months, or <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  4 years</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to get all my AA points.  Isn't that a tad difficult?  Ya I know there are some I'd never get, like +INT.   So maybe 3 years.  <br><br>And my gear isn't bad either so I'm not leveling slow.  Fiery Defender, Vox/Gore Haste Belt, etc., 